news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP extends deadline for revised PG norms to September 21
news.para: BBMP had initially set a Sept 15 deadline, warning that failure to comply would draw action under Sections 307 and 308 of the 2020 BBMP Act. The guidelines include a requirement of 70 sqft per person and a 90-day retention period for CCTV footage — measures strongly opposed by the PG Owners' Welfare Development Association.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body revises terms for auction of 13 plots
news.para: The AMC has revised its tender for the auction of 13 plots in the city, which was initially announced on Aug 22. The new terms stipulate that buyers pay 10% of the amount within 10 days and the remaining 90% within 90 days.

news.title: Ahmedabad: SRFDCL engages with global builders ahead of auction for riverfront plots
news.para: ​​This strategic push was detailed in the annual audit report presented to the SRFDCL board on Sep 6, just before the Request for Proposal (RFP) was announced for the auction of two prime plots. The riverfront project, spanning 204.91 hectares, is set to make a significant impact.
